<div type="translation" resp="part:emfr">
								
	<p n="1">Prosperity! Fortune!</p>
	<p n="1-4">29th year of the king Sundara Pāṇḍya.</p>
	<p n="4-11">This stone<note>That is, the pillar on which this inscription is engraved.</note> is the pious donation <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>dharma</foreign></supplied> of the Veḷḷāḷar Nilaiyiṭṭāṉ Cokki, magnate of/at Vaḷḷimantam, from Rājāśrayacaturvedimaṅgala, <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Cēlam.</p>
</div>
	
